    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 John",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "The sons of God will become like Christ\u2014Love for others is required to gain eternal life\u2014Obedience ensures us an answer to our prayers.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Behold, what manner of love the Father hath bestowed upon us, that we should be called the sons of God: therefore the world knoweth us not, because it knew him not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Love of.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0children, people. Isa. 56:5.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Beloved, now are we the sons of God, and it doth not yet appear what we shall be: but we know that, when he shall appear, we shall be like him; for we shall see him as he is.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0children, people. TG\u00a0Sons and Daughters of God.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 3:4. TG\u00a0God, Body of, Corporeal Nature.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 120
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:19 (14, 19); Moro. 7:48 (47\u201348). TG\u00a0Eternal Life; Man, Potential to Become like Heavenly Father; Resurrection.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 138
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 19:26 (25\u201327). TG\u00a0God, Privilege of Seeing.",
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 160
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1558
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And every man that hath this hope in him purifieth himself, even as he is pure.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hope; Motivations.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastity; Purification; Purity.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 5:21; 1\u00a0Pet. 1:16 (15\u201319); 2\u00a0Ne. 31:5 (5\u20137).",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whosoever committeth sin transgresseth also the law: for sin is the transgression of the law.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye know that he was manifested to take away our sins; and in him is no sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive; Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Jesus Christ, Redeemer.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whosoever abideth in him sinneth not: whosoever sinneth hath not seen him, neither known him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a01\u00a0Jn. 3:6 \u2026 whosoever continueth in sin hath not seen\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 2:4.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Little children, let no man deceive you: he that doeth righteousness is righteous, even as he is righteous.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that committeth sin is of the devil; for the devil sinneth from the beginning. For this purpose the Son of God was manifested, that he might destroy the works of the devil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a01\u00a0Jn. 3:8 \u2026 continueth in sin\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:1.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Devil.",
                        "start": 169,
                        "end": 174
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whosoever is born of God doth not commit sin; for his seed remaineth in him: and he cannot sin, because he is born of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, New, Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a01\u00a0Jn. 3:9 \u2026 doth not continue in sin; for the Spirit of God remaineth in him; and he cannot continue in sin, because he is born of God, having received that holy Spirit of promise.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In this the children of God are manifest, and the children of the devil: whosoever doeth not righteousness is not of God, neither he that loveth not his brother.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0conspicuous, apparent.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:44; Acts 13:10.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:20.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For this is the message that ye heard from the beginning, that we should love one another.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0precept, doctrine.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Not as Cain, who was of that wicked one, and slew his brother. And wherefore slew he him? Because his own works were evil, and his brother's righteous.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jude 1:11 (7\u201313).",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Marvel not, my brethren, if the world hate you.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We know that we have passed from death unto life, because we love the brethren. He that loveth not his brother abideth in death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 5:24.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 8:12; 1\u00a0Tim. 6:2; D&C 45:5; 108:7. TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Death, Spiritual, First.",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 127
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whosoever hateth his brother is a murderer: and ye know that no murderer hath eternal life abiding in him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 109:5 (3\u20135). TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Life, Sanctity of; Murder.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hereby perceive we the love of God, because he laid down his life for us: and we ought to lay down our lives for the brethren.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 10:15 (14\u201315); 15:13; 1\u00a0Ne. 11:22 (22, 25).",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But whoso hath this world's good, and seeth his brother have need, and shutteth up his bowels of compassion from him, how dwelleth the love of God in him?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 4:20 (20\u201321).",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 3:11.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0is hardhearted, void of compassion. TG\u00a0Hardheartedness.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My little children, let us not love in word, neither in tongue; but in deed and in truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a01\u00a0Jn. 3:18 \u2026 neither in tongue only\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And hereby we know that we are of the truth, and shall assure our hearts before him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For if our heart condemn us, God is greater than our heart, and knoweth all things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Intelligence of.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Beloved, if our heart condemn us not, then have we confidence toward God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:27.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And whatsoever we ask, we receive of him, because we keep his commandments, and do those things that are pleasing in his sight.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 2:3.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Good Works.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And this is his commandment, That we should believe on the name of his Son Jesus Christ, and love one another, as he gave us commandment.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commandments of God.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 25:20; Mosiah 3:17; D&C 11:30; 20:29. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Taking the Name of.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he that keepeth his commandments dwelleth in him, and he in him. And hereby we know that he abideth in us, by the Spirit which he hath given us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 6:56; Rom. 8:9; 1\u00a0Cor. 2:16; 2\u00a0Cor. 13:5; 1\u00a0Jn. 4:13 (7\u201321).",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 14:23.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 2:10; 1\u00a0Thes. 4:8.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}